3780	## Tailwind CSS
3781	
3782	Tailwind CSS uses a CSS-first configuration, letting you define your design tokens with the [`@theme`](https://tailwindcss.com/docs/functions-and-directives#theme-directive){rel="&#x22;nofollow&#x22;"} directive directly in your CSS. This makes your theme portable, maintainable and easy to customize.
3783	
3784	```css [app/assets/css/main.css]
3785	@import "tailwindcss";
3786	@import "@nuxt/ui";
3787	
3788	@theme {
3789	  /* Your custom design tokens go here */
3790	}
3791	```
3792	
3793	\> \[!NOTE]
3794	\> See: https\://tailwindcss.com/docs/theme
3795	\> Check the Tailwind CSS documentation for all available theme variable customization options.
3796	
3797	### Fonts
3798	
3799	Use the `--font-*` theme variables to [customize the font family utilities](https://tailwindcss.com/docs/font-family#customizing-your-theme){rel="&#x22;nofollow&#x22;"} in your project.
3800	
3801	```css [app/assets/css/main.css]
3802	@import "tailwindcss";
3803	@import "@nuxt/ui";
3804	
3805	@theme {
3806	  --font-sans: 'Public Sans', system-ui, sans-serif;
3807	  --font-mono: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
3808	}
3809	```
3810	
3811	\*\*Nuxt:\*\*
3812	\> \[!NOTE]
3813	\> See: /docs/getting-started/integrations/fonts
3814	\> Fonts defined here are automatically loaded and optimized by the \`@nuxt/fonts\` module.
3815	
3816	### Colors
3817	
3818	Use the `--color-*` theme variables to [customize your colors](https://tailwindcss.com/docs/colors#customizing-your-colors){rel="&#x22;nofollow&#x22;"} or [override default colors](https://tailwindcss.com/docs/colors#overriding-default-colors){rel="&#x22;nofollow&#x22;"}.
3819	
3820	```css [app/assets/css/main.css]
3821	@import "tailwindcss";
3822	@import "@nuxt/ui";
3823	
3824	@theme static {
3825	  /* Override default green color */
3826	  --color-green-50: #EFFDF5;
3827	  --color-green-100: #D9FBE8;
3828	  --color-green-200: #B3F5D1;
3829	  --color-green-300: #75EDAE;
3830	  --color-green-400: #00DC82;
3831	  --color-green-500: #00C16A;
3832	  --color-green-600: #00A155;
3833	  --color-green-700: #007F45;
3834	  --color-green-800: #016538;
3835	  --color-green-900: #0A5331;
3836	  --color-green-950: #052E16;
3837	
3838	  /* Define new custom color */
3839	  --color-brand-50: #fef2f2;
3840	  --color-brand-100: #fee2e2;
3841	  --color-brand-200: #fecaca;
3842	  --color-brand-300: #fca5a5;
3843	  --color-brand-400: #f87171;
3844	  --color-brand-500: #ef4444;
3845	  --color-brand-600: #dc2626;
3846	  --color-brand-700: #b91c1c;
3847	  --color-brand-800: #991b1b;
3848	  --color-brand-900: #7f1d1d;
3849	  --color-brand-950: #450a0a;
3850	}
3851	```
3852	
3853	\> \[!WARNING]
3854	\> When adding custom colors, make sure to define all shades from \`50\` to \`950\` for each color.
3855	
3856	### Breakpoints
3857	
3858	Use the `--breakpoint-*` theme variables to [customize your breakpoints](https://tailwindcss.com/docs/responsive-design#customizing-your-theme){rel="&#x22;nofollow&#x22;"}.
3859	
3860	```css [app/assets/css/main.css]
3861	@import "tailwindcss";
3862	@import "@nuxt/ui";
3863	
3864	@theme {
3865	  --breakpoint-3xl: 1920px;
3866	  --breakpoint-4xl: 2560px;
3867	  --breakpoint-5xl: 3840px;
3868	}
3869	```
3870	
3871	## Colors
3872	
3873	Nuxt UI's color system is designed around **semantic naming** rather than specific color values. This approach makes your UI more maintainable and allows for easy theme switching.
3874	
3875	### Semantic colors
3876	
3877	Nuxt UI provides semantic color aliases that describe the **purpose** of the color. Each alias is defined based on a color from your `@theme` configuration, which can be any color you define in addition to the [default Tailwind CSS palette](https://tailwindcss.com/docs/colors){rel="&#x22;nofollow&#x22;"}.
3878	
3879	| Color                          | Default  | Description                                                       |
3880	| ------------------------------ | -------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------- |
3881	| `primary`{color="primary"}     | `green`  | Main CTAs, active navigation, brand elements, important links     |
3882	| `secondary`{color="secondary"} | `blue`   | Secondary buttons, alternative actions, complementary UI elements |
3883	| `success`{color="success"}     | `green`  | Success messages, completed states, positive confirmations        |
3884	| `info`{color="info"}           | `blue`   | Info alerts, tooltips, help text, neutral notifications           |
3885	| `warning`{color="warning"}     | `yellow` | Warning messages, pending states, attention-needed items          |
3886	| `error`{color="error"}         | `red`    | Error messages, validation errors, destructive actions            |
3887	| `neutral`                      | `slate`  | Text, borders, backgrounds, disabled states                       |
3888	
3889	These semantic colors are available in the `color` prop of Nuxt UI components:
3890	
3891	```vue
3892	<template>
3893	  <UDesign System color="primary">
3894	    Save Changes
3895	  </UDesign System>
3896	</template>
3897	```
3898	
3899	\> \[!NOTE]

